Morphological description. Following description based on female specimen from Francis Drake III, Stn 2. Male description based on that of Rose (1929) (as
Ba. rigidus
), and male, USNM 122568 , augmented by observations made on material held at the Natural History Museum, London. As for genus with following specific level features.

Male (Fig. A–D). (From Rose, 1929 , pp. 9–14, Pl. 1, 25 figs (as
Ba. rigidus
) and male USNM 122568 , augmented by observations made on material held at the Natural History Museum, London). Total length: mean = 9.6 mm , range = 8.9–11.0 mm, n = 50. Anterior margin of head in dorsal and lateral views rounded, without crest. Rostrum ventrally-directed, bluntly tapering.
